page.title: 17LANDSCAPE.
page.content: { Jubilee Terrace Garden.}B.R.built a high concrete wall in front of the houses in Jubilee Terrace.When people look out of their windows it is miserable and dull.The path was changed into a garden so that the wall would be bright,living and cheerful.St.Barnabas' School volunteered to care for the garden. There is a new{flood barrier}near Clifton Ings because the{River Ouse flooded into all the houses.There is a big wall in front of the houses in Earlsborough Terrace to stop the river flooding them. { Our hedge}is in Ousecliffe Gardens at Clifton.We have gone to the hedge every Monday since September.We look at the trees and other things,and we do the temperature.We have planted daffodils there.
